COMPONENT NAME: LKM Siebel to SQL (EIM) COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 10.1.3.5.0 and above
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a Siebel EIM (Enterprise Integration Manager) table to any ISO-92 compliant target database. - This module uses the Sunopsis Agent to read selected data EIM (Enterprise Integration Manager) Siebel table and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically. - It is able to generate the appropriate EIM configuration files (.ifb) and runs the export process using the server Manager.
Restriction: - This module require srvrmgr on the machine where the agent runs.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Path to create the EIM configuration files (.ifb). This parameter is mandatory.
Path to the srvrmgr binary. This parameter is mandatory.
Network address of the Gateway Server machine. This parameter is mandatory.
Enterprise Server name. This parameter is mandatory.
Siebel Server name (default is all servers). This parameter is mandatory.
Server administrator user name. This parameter is mandatory.
Server administrator password. This parameter is mandatory.

import os # #Mandatory Option # SIEBEL_GATEWAY = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SIEBEL_GATEWAY")%>' SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE")%>' SIEBEL_SERVER = '<%=snpRef.getOption("SIEBEL_SERVER")%>' SERVER_USER = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SERVER_USER")%>' SERVER_USER_PWD = '<%=odiRef.getOption("SERVER_USER_PWD")%>' SRVRMGR_PATH =r'<%=odiRef.getOption("SRVRMGR_PATH")%>' IFB_PATH =r'<%=odiRef.getOption("IFB_PATH")%>' TABLE_NAME = '<%=odiRef.getSrcTablesList("","[TABLE_NAME]", ", ", "")%>' STARTTASK = r'run task for component eim with config=%s/%s_EXPORT.ifb , TraceFlags=1, ErrorFlags=1, SQLFlags=8' %( IFB_PATH, TABLE_NAME)
cmd = '''%s/SRVRMGR -g %s -e %s -s %s -u %s -p %s -c "%s" ''' %(SRVRMGR_PATH,SIEBEL_GATEWAY, SIEBEL_ENTERPRISE, SIEBEL_SERVER, SERVER_USER, SERVER_USER_PWD, STARTTASK) if os.system(cmd) <> 0 : raise "SRVRMGR error", "Error executing OS command: %s" %cmd

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
